INSERT INTO `Directions` (RecipeID, SortOrder, Direction) VALUES ('4308', '14', 'Combine greens and vinegar. Arrange 1 cup greens on each of 4 plates. top each with 1 cup lentils. Arrange 3 sardines on each plate.'),
('4311', '1', 'Arrange the sardines, skin side down, in a shallow glass or ceramic baking dish just large enough to hold them in a single layer. Scatter the sliced garlic and parsley sprigs all over the sardines.'),
('4311', '2', 'Pour 6 tablespoons of the olive oil along with the lemon juice on the sardine fillets, cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate, for at least 2 but not more than 6 hours.'),
('4311', '3', 'Drain the sardines, discarding the parsley and garlic, and pat dry.'),
('4311', '4', 'Transfer the sardines to a baking sheet.'),
('4311', '5', 'In a small bowl, toss the chopped tomatoes with the remaining 2 tablespoons of olive oil. Season the tomatoes with salt and pepper.'),
('4311', '6', 'Preheat the broiler. Toast the bread on both sides until golden and crisp. Rub the toast with the whole garlic clove, drizzle lightly with oil and transfer to a platter.'),
('4311', '7', 'Heat the sardines under the broiler for 20 to 30 seconds, or just until slightly warm. be careful not to cook the fish. Spoon the tomatoes on the bread and top with the fish. Sprinkle with salt and pepper and serve right away.'),
('4313', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 37'),
('4313', '2', 'Brush the cut sides of the eggplant with 2 tablespoons of olive oil and place cut side down on a rimmed baking sheet.'),
('4313', '3', 'Bake the eggplant for about 45 minutes, until very soft.'),
('4313', '4', 'Let cool, then carefully scoop out the flesh and coarsely chop it.'),
('4313', '5', 'Transfer the eggplant to a medium bowl.'),
('4313', '6', 'In a small saucepan, combine the vinegar with the water, 2 tablespoons of the tarragon, half of the shallot and two-thirds of the garlic and bring to a boil. Simmer over low heat until nearly evaporated, about 5 minutes.'),
('4313', '7', 'Transfer the mixture to a blender.'),
('4313', '8', 'Add the chicken stock and one-fourth of the eggplant and puree until smooth. Stir the puree into the remaining chopped eggplant and season with salt and pepper.'),
('4313', '9', 'In a small skillet, toast the pine nuts over moderately high heat, shaking the pan occasionally, until golden, about 3 minutes. transfer to a plate. In the same skillet, heat the remaining 1/4 cup of olive oil.'),
('4313', '10', 'Add the remaining shallot and garlic and cook over low heat until softened, about 2 minutes.'),
('4313', '11', 'Transfer the shallot and garlic to a bowl and let cool.'),
('4313', '12', 'Whisk in the lemon zest, roasted red pepper, capers and lemon juice and season with salt and pepper. Stir in the remaining 1/4 cup of tarragon and the pine nuts.'),
('4313', '13', 'Preheat a grill.'),
('4313', '14', 'Brush the sardines with olive oil and season both sides generously with salt and pepper. Grill the sardines over high heat, turning them once, until lightly charred, 2 to 3 minutes. Spoon the eggplant puree onto plates and top with the sardines. Spoon the tarragon dressing on top and serve.'),
('4320', '1', 'Cook the rice in a large saucepan of lightly salted boiling water for about 20 minutes, or until just tender.'),
('4320', '2', 'Drain, rinse under cold running water, and drain again.'),
('4320', '3', 'Combine the rice, pine nuts, currants, parsley, mint, dill, and lemon juice. Season with salt and a pinch of cayenne pepper.'),
('4320', '4', 'Divide the stuffing among the sardines, packing firmly into each cavity. Tightly overwrap each sardine with a vine leaf.'),
('4320', '5', 'Brush lightly with the olive oil.'),
('4320', '6', 'Preheat a broiler or build a hot fire in an outdoor grill. Broil or grill the sardines, turning once, for 4-5 minutes, until the sardine flesh is opaque (open one to check).'),
('4320', '7', 'Transfer the fish to a platter.'),
('4320', '8', 'Serve hot, with the lemon wedges.'),
('4320', '9', 'var article'),
('4320', '10', 'Type_27_data = {}.'),
('4320', '11', 'article'),
('4320', '12', 'Type_27_data.init_step_by_step_images = 0.'),
('4322', '1', 'In a medium bowl stir together chickpeas, cucumber, feta, olives, lemon zest and juice, mint and 1 tablespoon of the olive oil. Arrange equal parts of salad base on six plates.Dredge sardines through flour mixture and set aside, ready to be fried.'),
('4322', '2', 'Heat remaining olive oil over medium heat in a fry-pan large enough to accommodate the sardines in one or two batches. When barely smoking, carefully lay in sardines, working in two batches if necessary to avoid crowding. Sizzle fish in oil about 30 seconds on each side then carefully transfer back to dry towel to drain.Stack three fillets on top of each salad and sprinkle with a pinch of chopped chives and a few cracks of black pepper.Related Broiled Sardines with Gremolata (including a sardine-cleaning tutorial) Text Message for Safe Fish Blue Ocean Institute''s Ocean-Friendly Seafood GuideA version of this post was originally sent to our email subscribers yesterday. To receive Sara Kate''s weekly email, sign up in the column to the left or click here. Something tasty will arrive in your inbox every Thursday.(Image by Sara Kate Gillingham-Ryan for TheKitchn.com)Show Nutritionsugar-consciousvegetarianegg-freepeanut-freetree-nut-freesoy-freefish-freeshellfish-free'),
('4322', '3', 'Per serving, based on6servings.(% daily value)Calories249Fat15 g(23.1%)Saturated3.4 g(17.2%)Carbs22.4 g(7.5%)Fiber0.7 g(3%)Sugars0.8 gProtein7.8 g(15.6%)Cholesterol11.1 mg(3.7%)Sodium787.8 mg(32.8%)'),
('4324', '1', 'In a medium saucepan, cover potatoes and garlic with water and season generously with salt. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer until potatoes are tender, 8 to 10 minutes.'),
('4324', '2', 'Drain, reserving 1 cup cooking water, and return to pan.'),
('4325', '1', 'Prepare a medium-hot grill fire. When hot, wipe down the grill with a paper towel dipped in oil.'),
('4325', '2', 'Cut 2 of the lemons into 1/4-inch slices and halve the other. Grill the lemon slices and halves until they have nice grill marks, 2 to 3 minutes per side for the slices and 3 minutes total for the halves. Then carefully grill the chiles until lightly charred, about 1 minute (if you have a mesh grill insert, use it to keep the chiles from falling through the grate). Mince one-quarter of the lemon slices and transfer to a small bowl. Chop the chiles into small pieces (for less heat, remove and discard the seeds first).'),
('4325', '3', 'Add the chiles to the bowl, along with the 1/2 cup olive oil, parsley, garlic, shallot, and 1/2 teaspoon salt.'),
('4325', '4', 'Whisk to blend and set aside. Season the sardines with 1 teaspoon salt and drizzle with a little olive oil. Grill, turning once, until the fish are just cooked through, about 2 minutes per side. Arrange the remaining three-quarters of the lemon slices on a platter and top with the grilled sardines.'),
('4325', '5', 'Drizzle the sauce over and around the sardines, reserving any extra to serve on the side. Squeeze the grilled lemon halves over the platter.'),
('4325', '6', 'Serve warm or at room temperature.'),
('4327', '1', 'Stir together yogurt, celery, chives, and mustard. Fold in sardines. Toss greens with lemon juice and olive oil. season with salt and pepper. Top with sardine salad.'),
('4329', '1', 'Preheat the grill or broiler.'),
('4329', '2', 'Heat the oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('4329', '3', 'Add the onions and pepper and cook over high heat for 4 minutes. Stir in the minced garlic and basil, cook for 30 seconds, then add the tomatoes. Simmer 15 minutes, or until thickened.'),
('4329', '4', 'Remove from heat and season to taste.'),
('4329', '5', 'Place the sardines on the hottest part of the grill and cook through, about 2 minutes per side. Meanwhile, divide the peperonata evenly among 4 warmed dinner plates and mound loosely in the center of each plate. Arrange the sardines over each mound of salad and ser'),
('4330', '1', 'Remove the sardines from the cans. Using a small, sharp knife, carefully open each one down the belly and back, folding them open to expose the backbone.'),
('4330', '2', 'Remove and discard the bones.'),
('4330', '3', 'Cut away and discard any tails. Set aside.2'),
('4330', '4', 'Place the cream cheese or Neufchtel in a medium bowl. Fold and stir with a rubber spatula until smooth.'),
('4330', '5', 'Add the shallots, scallions, fresh herbs, and most of the lime or lemon juice, mixing into the cheese with the spatula.3'),
('4330', '6', 'Add the now boneless sardines to the cheese mixture. Use a fork to smash the sardines and stir into the cheese.'),
('4330', '7', 'Add cayenne, salt, and pepper to taste.'),
('4330', '8', 'Add more lime or lemon juice to taste.Either serve immediately (Dorie suggests chilling at least 2 hours, but I haven''t found that necessary), or chill. Can make up to two days ahead if you carefully cover with plastic wrap so there is no exposure to air, and chill.'),
('4330', '9', 'Serve on crackers, bread, celery sticks, or as a stuffing for cherry tomatoes.'),
('4331', '1', 'Heat 1 tablespoon oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('4331', '2', 'Add onions. season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until golden, about 18 minutes. (Reduce heat if onions become too dark.)'),
('4332', '1', 'Rinse the sardines inside and out and pat with paper towels. Insert a sprig of thyme inside each fish.'),
('4332', '2', 'Place them in a shallow nonmetallic dish. Grate the zest and squeeze the juice from 3 of the lemons.'),
('4332', '3', 'Whisk the lemon zest and juice, oil, cumin, and garlic together in a bowl.'),
('4332', '4', 'Pour over the sardines. Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.'),
('4332', '5', 'Preheat the broiler.'),
('4332', '6', 'Transfer the sardines to an oiled broiler rack, reserving the mariande. Broil for 2-3 minutes on each side, basting with the marinade.'),
('4332', '7', 'Thinly slice the remaining lemon.'),
('4332', '8', 'Transfer the sardines to a serving platter and serve immediately, garnished with the lemon wedges and more thyme sprigs.'),
('4332', '9', 'var article'),
('4332', '10', 'Type_27_data = {}.'),
('4332', '11', 'article'),
('4332', '12', 'Type_27_data.init_step_by_step_images = 0.'),
('4335', '1', 'Cook pasta according to package directions. drain.'),
('4335', '2', 'Trim outer leaves from fennel. Chop fronds to measure 1/2 cup. Discard stalks.'),
('4335', '3', 'Cut bulb in half lengthwise. discard core. Thinly slice bulb.'),
('4335', '4', 'Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('4335', '5', 'Add sliced fennel and onion. saut 4 minutes.'),
('4335', '6', 'Add garlic. saut 20 seconds. Stir in tomato sauce, oregano, red pepper, and sauce from sardines. Cover and reduce heat.'),
('4335', '7', 'Discard backbones from fish.'),
('4335', '8', 'Add fish to pan. gently break fish into chunks. Cover and cook 6 minutes. Toss pasta with sauce. sprinkle with fronds.'),
('4337', '1', 'Divide lettuce, tomatoes, carrots, radishes, hard-boiled eggs, cheeses and ham among 4 large salad bowls.'),
('4337', '2', 'In a bowl, whisk vinegar, honey, Dijon, salt and pepper.'),
('4337', '3', 'Whisking constantly, drizzle in oil until mixture is combined.'),
('4337', '4', 'Serve salads, passing dressing on the side.'),
('4338', '1', 'Steam damp spinach in a largecovered pot over medium heatuntil tender and wilted, about5 minutes.'),
('4338', '2', 'Drain. Squeeze outexcess water.'),
('4338', '3', 'Transfer to a foodprocessor.'),
('4338', '4', 'Add garlic, pepperflakes, nuts, and Parmesan tobowl. Pulse until finely ground.With machine running, add oil.Stir in lemon zest. Season withsalt.'),
('4338', '5', 'Serve with toasted breaddrizzled with oil and topped withsardines and currants. Squeezewith lemon before serving.'),
('4342', '1', 'Heat oven to 400 degrees. On a rimmed baking sheet, arrange prosciutto in a single layer and brush with remaining tablespoon oil.'),
('4342', '2', 'Bake, rotating halfway through, until crisp and deep golden brown, about 9 minutes.'),
('4343', '1', 'Stir together sour cream, horseradish, dill, and salt to taste.'),
('4343', '2', 'Cut beets into 1/2-inch cubes and toss with oil and salt to taste.'),
('4343', '3', 'Serve sardines on top of beets with sour cream mixture.'),
('4344', '1', 'Cut the pork into 2 1/2" squares.'),
('4344', '2', 'Put the pork belly, fat side down, in a small heavy bottomed pot (such as a dutch oven) that''s just large enough to hold the pork in a single layer.'),
('4344', '3', 'Put the pot over medium high heat and let the pork fry undisturbed until it''s golden brown on the fat side.Flip each piece over and brown the other side, then transfer to a plate.'),
('4344', '4', 'Add the ginger, garlic, and niboshi and and fry until browned and fragrant.'),
('4344', '5', 'Add the sake and boil until you no longer smell alcohol.'),
('4344', '6', 'Add the water, sugar, soy sauce, salt, and return the pork to the pot. Bring to a simmer and then turn down the heat and cover with a tight fitting lid.Simmer until the pork belly is fall-apart-tender (about 2 hours).Strain the braising liquid and if you are going to serve the kakuni right away, skim off the extra fat. It''s best if you let this sit in the fridge overnight though as this gives the meat a chance to absorb more flavor, and it will make removing the excess fat a lot easier.To serve, gently reheat the pork belly. Slice and serve with some of the braising liquid, hot mustard and steamed greens.'),
('4345', '1', 'In large shallow skillet over moderately high heat, heat 3 inches of oil until thermometer registers 350F.'),
('4345', '2', 'Transfer flour to large plate. Sprinkle all seafood liberally with salt and pepper. Working in batches and returning oil to 350F between batches, dredge seafood in flour, shaking to remove excess, and fry until golden and cooked through, about 20 seconds per side for whole fish and shrimp, 15 seconds per side for scallops and calamari. Using slotted spoon, remove as done and drain on paper towellined plate.'),
('4345', '3', 'Garnish with lemon wedges and serve immediately with tartar sauce.'),
('4346', '1', 'Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil.'),
('4346', '2', 'Add pasta, and cook for about 8 minutes, or until almost tender.'),
('4346', '3', 'While the pasta is cooking, heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat.'),
('4346', '4', 'Add the onion, and cook for a few minutes until soft, then add the garlic, and cook until fragrant. Stir in the sardines with their sauce. When the sardines heat through, reduce heat to low, and simmer until the pasta is ready.'),
('4346', '5', 'When the pasta is almost done, drain, and add it to the sardine sauce. Stir, cover, and turn the heat off.'),
('4346', '6', 'Let stand for a few minutes to absorb the flavors of the sauce. Squeeze juice from the lemon over the pasta. Divide onto serving plates, and top with red pepper flakes and grated Parmesan cheese.'),
('4348', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 40'),
('4348', '2', 'Fill a large bowl with water and squeeze the lemon into it. Snap off the green outer leaves of the artichokes until you reach the yellow leaves.'),
('4348', '3', 'Cut off the top third of each artichoke. Using a mandoline or a food processor fitted with the slicing blade, thinly shave the artichokes.'),
('4348', '4', 'Add them to the lemon water. Shave the sunchokes into the lemon water.'),
('4348', '5', 'In a very large ovenproof skillet, heat the canola oil until nearly smoking. Season the sardines lightly with salt and pepper and add them to the skillet. Cook for 3 minutes, then flip the sardines and add the garlic, olives, parsley, oregano, capers, chiles and lemon zest.'),
('4348', '6', 'Transfer the skillet to the oven and roast the sardines for about 5 minutes, or until cooked through.'),
('4348', '7', 'Drain the artichokes and sunchokes and pat dry. Return them to the bowl and add the arugula, olive oil and lemon juice. Season lightly with salt and pepper.'),
('4348', '8', 'Transfer the sardines and salad to plates and serve.'),
('4351', '1', 'Heat the butter and olive oil in a large skillet over medium-low heat.'),
('4351', '2', 'Add the onions and cook gently for 20 minutes until very soft and just beginning to turn golden.'),
('4351', '3', 'In the meantime, drain, bone and finely chop the sardines.  Bring a pot of salty water to boil.'),
('4351', '4', 'When the onions are cooked, add the sardines and a splash of water to the onions and heat through.'),
('4351', '5', 'Add the milk and bring to a slight boil, then turn the heat to a simmer and cook until the sardines melt and the sauce thickens, 5 to 10 minutes.'),
('4351', '6', 'Cook the pasta until al dente.'),
('4351', '7', 'Drain and add to the sauce, reserving some pasta water in case it gets dry.  Toss to coat, season with salt and lots of pepper, and serve.'),
('4352', '1', 'Drain the oil from 1 tin of sardines into a small bowl and set aside.'),
('4352', '2', 'Drain the oil from the second tin into another small bowl and mix it with 1 tablespoon of parsley, vinegar, lemon zest, and black pepper.'),
('4352', '3', 'Add the sardines and stir.'),
('4352', '4', 'Let sit for a bit so the flavors marry.'),
('4352', '5', 'Toast your bread in a normal toaster or, if you want to be all Alton-style fancy, heat the oven to the broiler setting on high and place oiled-swiped bread (using the remaining sardine oil) on the rack. Only keep them in there for 2 to 3 minutes, otherwise they will go from golden brown and crisp to charred and sad.'),
('4352', '6', 'Halve the avocado and remove the pit. Smoosh the flesh in each half with a fork.'),
('4352', '7', 'Spread this green goodness evenly onto the toasted bread, then top with a nice scoop of the sardine mixture.'),
('4352', '8', 'Pour any remaining sardine oil dressing on top and garnish with the remaining parsley. Season with sea salt and a nice big squeeze from the lemon wedges.'),
('4357', '1', 'Preheat oven to 45'),
('4357', '2', 'Mix mayo ingredients in a small bowl. chill. Cook bacon until crisp in a 12-in. frying pan, transfer to paper towels, and reserve fat in pan.'),
('4357', '3', 'Cook sardines skin side down in fat (in 2 batches if needed) over medium-high heat until opaque, tipping pan often and spooning fat over fish.'),
('4357', '4', 'Drain fish on paper towels.'),
('4357', '5', 'Spread rolls with parsley chive mayo. Layer arugula, tomatoes, bacon, and sardines in rolls and cut in half.'),
('4357', '6', '*Ask your fishmonger to clean and fillet sardines for you, or do it yourself (see "How to Clean and Fillet Sardines" at sunset.com/smartseafood).'),
('4358', '1', 'Make the sofrito. In a large cazuela or medium Dutch oven or another heavy pot, heat the oil over medium-low heat.'),
('4358', '2', 'Add the onion and cook until soft and nearly translucent, 5 to 10 minutes.'),
('4358', '3', 'Add the garlic, tomatoes, and 2 pinches of salt and cook, stirring from time to time, until the tomato has darkened to a deeper shade of red and the sofrito is pasty, 10 to 15 minutes.'),
('4358', '4', 'Preheat oven to 400F.'),
('4358', '5', 'When the sofrito is ready, sprinkle in the pimentn and saffron, letting the flavors meld for a few seconds while stirring constantly.'),
('4358', '6', 'Add the stock, increase the heat, and bring to a boil.'),
('4358', '7', 'Add the rice and peas. With a wooden spoon, probe the pan to make sure the rice is evenly distributed. Check for salt, adjusting the seasoning as needed.'),
('4358', '8', 'Cook, uncovered, over medium-high heat for 10 minutes, gently stirring occasionally.'),
('4358', '9', 'Remove from the heat.'),
('4358', '10', 'Working quickly, lay the sardines across the top of the rice like spokes on a wheel, cover loosely with aluminum foil, and place in the hot oven.'),
('4358', '11', 'Bake until most of the liquid is absorbed (it doesnt need to be dry), the rice is al punto, with just a bite to it, and the eyes of the sardines are cloudy, about 10 minutes.'),
('4358', '12', 'Remove the cazuela from the oven and immediately transfer the food to plates, letting the rice rest for a few minutes before serving.'),
('4358', '13', 'var article'),
('4358', '14', 'Type_27_data = {}.'),
('4358', '15', 'article'),
('4358', '16', 'Type_27_data.init_step_by_step_images = 0.'),
('4360', '1', 'Heat oil in a 10-inch heavy skillet over moderate heat until hot but not smoking, then cook fennel, onion, preserved lemon rind, fennel seeds, salt, and pepper, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes.'),
('4360', '2', 'Add water and braise, covered, stirring occasionally, until fennel is very tender and slightly caramelized and water is evaporated, about 10 minutes. Keep warm, covered.'),
('4364', '1', 'Combine all ingredients in food processor except than the soy oil. Turn on and slowly drizzle oil in until emulsion is formed. Season with salt and lemon juice as needed.  For the fish:  When ready to serve, season whitefish with salt and pepper and bury in the flour. Gently remove the fish from the flour, shake off any excess and drop into a 375 F fryer until crispy and golden. Quickly remove onto paper towels and again season with kosher salt.'),
('4364', '2', 'Serve in bowl with aioli as dipping sauce.'),
('4365', '1', 'SARDE EN SAOR (VENETIAN-STYLE SARDINES)serves 2MARINADE2 tablespoons olive oil1 cup thinly sliced onions2/3 cup balsamic vinegar2 generous tablespoons sugar2 tablespoons golden raisins, chopped1 bay leaflarge pinch saffron cup pine nuts, toastedSARDINES6 whole fresh sardines, cleaned, gutted and scaledall-purpose flour (I used rice flour to good effect)olive oil, for fryinglemon wedges'),
('4365', '2', 'Heat the oil in a sautee pan and cook the onions until they are soft and pale gold.'),
('4365', '3', 'Remove from heat and transfer to a large shallow bowl.'),
('4365', '4', 'Combine vinegar, sugar, raisins and bay leaf in a small saucepan and crumble in saffron.'),
('4365', '5', 'Heat over low flame, stirring until sugar is dissolved, reducing slightly.'),
('4365', '6', 'Pour over onions. Stir in pine nuts.Wash your sardines and pat dry. Salt them and lightly dredge in flour.'),
('4365', '7', 'Heat a generous amount of oil in a large skillet and, when oil is hot but not smoking, fry sardines until golden brown, about 2 minutes per side. Dont crowd pan. fry in batches if necessary.'),
('4365', '8', 'Place the fried sardines in the marinade and spoon it over so they are well covered.The sardines can be eaten now, with a squeeze of lemon, alongside a simple fennel salad and grilled white polenta. Or they can continue to marinate in the refrigerator for a day or two and be served cold as part of a larger antipasto.Tagged main course, Italian, fish, sardines, fish oil, sarde en saor, marinated fish, sweet &amp. sour, canned fish, canned sardines, fresh sardines'),
('4365', '9', 'TweetBACK TO LISTNEXT ENTRYPREVIOUS ENTRY'),
('4367', '1', 'Bring a large saucepan of salted water to a boil. Boil broccoli rabe for 1 -2 minutes. remove and plunge into a bowl of ice water. Shocking the rabe will maintain its vivid green color and stop it from cooking. Using the same pan, bring the water to a boil again, and add the pasta. Cook until al dente.'),
('4367', '2', 'Place the raisins in a small bowl and cover with some dry white wine.'),
('4367', '3', 'Let them soak about 10 minutes to become infused with the flavor of the wine.'),
('4367', '4', 'In a small, dry skillet over medium heat add the pine nuts and breadcrumbs. Shake pan in a back-and-forth motion until they are are golden and aromatic, about 1-2 minutes.'),
('4367', '5', 'Remove from heat and set aside.'),
('4367', '6', 'In a large skillet over medium heat, warm 2 tablespoons olive oil.'),
('4367', '7', 'Add garlic and shallots, sauteing 2-3 minutes, or until lightly browned.'),
('4367', '8', 'Drain the broccoli rabe, pat dry, and add to the skillet.'),
('4367', '9', 'Drain the sardines. Using a fork, break sardines into small pieces and add to the skillet.'),
('4367', '10', 'Add the drained raisins, olives, lemon juice, lemon zest, crushed red pepper, and salt. Saut 1-2 minutes more.'),
('4367', '11', 'Remove from heat.'),
('4367', '12', 'Add cooked pasta to the skillet with the broccoli rabe mixture.'),
('4367', '13', 'Add toasted bread crumb mixture and fresh parsley and toss.'),
('4367', '14', 'Drizzle with quality extra virgin olive oil before serving.'),
('4368', '1', 'Preheat oven to 350F.Flake sardines with a fork into a mixing bowl. (The pieces should not be mashed, but should be no bigger than a dime.)'),
('4368', '2', 'Add mint, oil and salt. toss gently to combine.If using whole slices of bread, cut off the crusts and cut each into four triangles.'),
('4368', '3', 'Place the triangles or baguette slices on a baking sheet and bake until crispy and golden brown, 12 to 14 minutes. As soon as you remove them from the oven, rub each slice with the cut side of the tomato. As you progress, the tomato will break down until only the skin remains. discard any remaining tomato.Top each toast with about 1 1/2 teaspoons of the sardine mixture. Top the sardine mixture with a couple of onion slices and serve immediately.'),
('4369', '1', 'Adjust the oven rack to the middle position and preheat the oven to 350F.'),
('4369', '2', 'Place the bread slices on a baking sheet, brush the tops with olive oil, and bake them for 15 to 20 minutes, until theyre lightly toasted and golden brown. (You can also toast the bread in a toaster, but without the oil. Then brush the toast with oil after theyre done.) Rub the oiled side of the crostini with the garlic and set them on your work surface, oiled side up.'),
('4369', '3', 'Spread about 2 teaspoons of butter in an uneven layer on each crostino, leaving the edges of the bread visible. Scatter the onion slices over the butter, dividing them evenly, lay 1 sardine on each, and top with the cress and a few grains of sea salt.'),
('4369', '4', 'var article'),
('4369', '5', 'Type_27_data = {}.'),
('4369', '6', 'article'),
('4369', '7', 'Type_27_data.init_step_by_step_images = 0.'),
('4370', '1', 'Bring a very large pot of heavily salted water to a boil.'),
('4370', '2', 'Open the sardine tin and drain a tablespoon or so of the oil into a wide skillet (the amount of oil in the tin will vary by brand, so add additional extra virgin olive oil if necessary to make up a tablespoon).  Warm the oil over medium-low heat and add the garlic, cooking until fragrant.'),
('4370', '3', 'Trim the fennel and slice the bulb very thinly (a mandoline works great here).'),
('4370', '4', 'Add to the skillet with a sprinkle of salt, raise the heat to medium, and cook until the fennel is soft and beginning to caramelize.'),
('4370', '5', 'Add the chile flakes and let them sizzle for a minute, just until fragrant, then add the tomatoes with their juice.  Cook until the liquid is reduced, then add the vermouth and let that reduce slightly.'),
('4370', '6', 'Add the sardines to the skillet with the tomato and fennel mixture, breaking up slightly but leaving some chunks.  Zest the lemon and combine a tablespoon or so of zest with the toasted breadcrumbs, then set aside. Juice the lemon and add the juice to the pan. Taste and adjust salt if necessary.'),
('4370', '7', 'Add the linguine to the boiling salted water, cooking it until it is just short of al dente.  Using tongs, transfer the linguine to the sauce to finish cooking, adding a little bit of the starchy pasta water and tossing gently to combine. (You''ll want to leave this a little wet, as the breadcrumbs will soak up the sauce and dry the pasta out a bit once you''ve added them.)'),
('4370', '8', 'Transfer the pasta and sauce to a large warmed serving bowl (or individual pasta bowls), add a drizzle of olive oil, sprinkle on the toasted breadcrumb-lemon zest mixture, and garnish with picked small fennel fronds and the remaining lemon zest.'),
('4377', '1', 'Put flour into a bowl and season with salt and pepper. Stir in the beer, 1/2 half at a time, whisking to work out any lumps.'),
('4377', '2', 'Add the egg yolk and mix well to combine. The batter should be the consistency of heavy cream.'),
('4377', '3', 'In a wok or deep fat fryer, heat a couple of inches of oil to 375 degrees F. Rinse and dry all ingredients to be fried. Fry the ingredients in the order listed. Coat ingredients with flour, shaking off the excess. Dip in batter and immediately place into hot oil. Do not overcrowd pan. Cook until golden: the herbs will cook quickly, the seafood will take a bit longer. Skim any loose pieces of batter from the oil.'),
('4377', '4', 'Drain on paper towels.'),
('4377', '5', 'Place on a large platter, season with salt and pepper, and squeeze over some lemon wedges.'),
('4377', '6', 'Serve immediately.'),
('4379', '1', 'The process: wash the watercress and maybe use a salad spinner to get water off. Slice the onions and tomato as thin as you can by hand and set aside. If you have a Kyocera hand slicer (remember mine is named Danton) use it to thinly slice the radishes.'),
('4379', '2', 'Assembly: lay out a large sheet of plastic wrap on a board. Slice the roll in half lengthwise.'),
('4379', '3', 'Put the halves on the cling wrap and scoop out enough of the crumb so that you have two canoes. Give both canoes a generous dose of your best olive oil.'),
('4379', '4', 'Place a good handful of leaves on the first canoe.  Top this with the sardine and then the anchovies.'),
('4379', '5', 'Add tomatoes and onion in any order you would like. Finish with olives and radishes, all in a big pile. In the other canoe place the remaining cress. And turn over to cover the sandwich.'),
('4379', '6', 'Wrap it all up in the cling wrap and refrigerate for a couple of hours. Repeat with as many rolls as you have.'),
('4380', '1', 'In a large bowl, mix the cilantro with the olive oil, grainy and Dijon mustards, red onion and the lemon juice and zest. Fold in the sardines and celery and season with salt and pepper. Chill and serve or pack in a plastic container.'),
('4382', '1', 'Cook pasta according to directions in salted water'),
('4382', '2', 'Combine sauce, clams, tomatoes and greens in a medium sauce pan.'),
('4382', '3', 'Heat to a simmer.'),
('4382', '4', 'Serve, garnishing with parm cheese'),
('4384', '1', 'Place the garlic and mint in a small saucepan with the wine vinegar and set over medium-low heat. As soon as the vinegar starts to boil, lower the heat to below a simmer and let the aromatics steep in the vinegar until ready to serve.'),
('4384', '2', 'Coat the bottom of a small saucepan, over medium-high heat, with about 1 tablespoon of the oil.'),
('4384', '3', 'Add the bread crumbs and toast until they are golden brown and crisp.'),
('4384', '4', 'Remove and set aside.'),
('4384', '5', 'Place the flour in a shallow bowl and add the fish, to lightly coat. In a large saute pan, over medium-high heat, add half of the remaining olive oil. Fry the fish on both sides until cooked through. As fish are fried, remove from the pan and drain on a paper towel lined platter.'),
('4384', '6', 'When all the fish have been fried, discard the oil and wipe out the pan.'),
('4384', '7', 'Add the remaining clean oil to the pan and set over very low heat to warm.'),
('4384', '8', 'Layer the fish in a glass or ceramic dish, sprinkling each layer liberally with the toasted bread crumbs and distributing the garlic and mint from the vinegar infusion. The top layer of bread crumbs should completely cover the fish.'),
('4384', '9', 'Combine the reserved warm vinegar and warm clean oil and pour over the bread crumbs. Cover the dish and refrigerate for 2 or 3 days before serving.'),
('4385', '1', 'Preheat grill to medium-high heat.'),
('4385', '2', 'To prepare fish, rinse fish with cold water. pat dry.'),
('4385', '3', 'Combine 1 teaspoon juice, turmeric, and 1/2 teaspoon salt. rub evenly over fish.'),
('4385', '4', 'Combine remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt, bell pepper, garlic, Thai chiles, and 1 shallot in a food processor. process until finely ground.'),
('4385', '5', 'Heat a small skillet over medium heat.'),
('4385', '6', 'Add 1 tablespoon oil to pan. swirl to coat.'),
('4385', '7', 'Add garlic mixture. cook 5 minutes or until mixture begins to brown, stirring frequently.'),
('4385', '8', 'Remove from heat. cool 15 minutes. Spoon 1 tablespoon garlic mixture into the cavity of each fish. Arrange fish on a grill rack coated with cooking spray. grill 2 minutes on each side or until desired degree of doneness.'),
('4385', '9', 'To prepare sauce, combine 1/3 cup shallots and remaining ingredients in a small bowl.'),
('4385', '10', 'Serve with fish.'),
('4388', '1', 'In a dry heavy skillet over medium heat, stir the sesame seeds and dried sardines until they give off their fragrance but don''t burn, about 2 minutes.'),
('4388', '2', 'Place the sesame seeds and dried sardines in the work bowl of a small food processor, and pulse until ground to a fine powder.'),
('4388', '3', 'Place the dried sardine mixture in a large bowl, and stir in the miso to make a very thick paste.'),
('4388', '4', 'Add boiling water and mix to a smooth, creamy consistency, and gently stir in the cubed tofu, green onions, and red pepper flakes.'),
('4390', '1', 'Clean and trim 1 bunch spinach.You want to break off the root end (see right hand), leaving just the leaves and as much stem as you tolerate (see left hand). You can save the root end for stock or compost'),
('4390', '2', 'In a food processor, puree together peanuts, dried sardines, and soumbala.Peanut pieces are much cheaper than whole peanuts, so I buy them in bulk for cooking.I couldnt find dried sardines, so I used smoked anchovies.You cant tell from the picture, but I was telling Keith to hurry up and take it already.He took his sweet time, relishing the sight of me squirming about with the fishies.I shouldnt have been so squeamish. Ive filleted fish. Ive boned a lamb shank (all at the Culinary Institute of America). But dried fish are on a whole other level.I guess thats what this Adventure is for.Hello little guys.'),
('4390', '3', 'Lets get acquainted!Heres the soumbala. It was frozen and I put it in the food processor that way with no problems. I really enjoyed this, despite the strong odor. But, then again, I love anything fermented  stinky cheese, wine, bread,Puree until the mixture looks like coarse sand. Or fine gravel.'),
('4390', '4', 'Add 1/2 cup white rice and process another 20 seconds.Some of the rice will break into smaller pieces which will contribute to the the characteristicgelatinoustexture of the final dish.'),
('4390', '5', 'Add all ingredients (including spinach) to large pot with water. Simmer, covered.After about 15 minutes, give everything a stir to mix the spinach in.Doesnt look too hot yet. Dont worry.Simmer another 15 minutes.The rice will have absorbed all the water, making for a pasty mass of spinach and rice.'),
('4390', '6', 'Serve immediately, with a confident smile.This recipe was fascinating! Thank you Burkina Faso Special Thanks to Jeannette M. who helped clarify my rusty translation from the French. Without her, I very well might have thought this was a beverage. Ok. Not really. But thank you Jeannette for suggesting what greens to use. Your time and cheerful assistance made my adaptation a success !Votes: 0Rating: 0You:Rate this recipe!Print Recipe'),
