('4392', '1', 'Place add all ingredients in small pan.'),
('4392', '2', 'Heat until done.'),
('4392', '3', 'Serve over hot rice.'),
('4394', '1', 'Preheat oven (390 F, 200 C).Cook Penne according to package directions, but only until hardly al dente.Meanwhile put 1 tablespoon of olive oil in an oven proof dish.Salt and pepper sardines to taste and arrange them in a single layer in the dish.'),
('4394', '2', 'Combine cream, tomato puree and thyme leaves. Salt and pepper to taste.When pasta are cooked drain them (but do not rinse them) and arrange them over the fish.'),
('4394', '3', 'Spread the cream-tomato mixture evenly over pasta. Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon of olive oil.Crumble feta cheese over the sauce.'),
('4394', '4', 'Place butter in little pieces on top and put in the oven.'),
('4394', '5', 'Bake for 25 minutes.'),
('4394', '6', 'Serve hot.NOTE: if you like it a bit more saucy use 3/4 cup of cream and 2 tablespoons of tomato puree.'),
('4395', '1', 'Lightly toast bread and spread with butter.Sprinkle with onion and top with sardines.'),
('4395', '2', 'Drizzle lemon juice and season with black pepper.'),
('4395', '3', 'Place under medium-low grill/broiler 2-3 minutes. (Watch carefully).'),
('4397', '1', 'To a large skillet preheated over medium heat, add 1/4 cup extra-virgin olive oil, 4 turns of the pan, and chopped garlic. When the garlic speaks by sizzling in oil add bread crumbs. Stir bread crumbs until deeply golden in color.'),
('4397', '2', 'Add parsley and a liberal amount of salt and pepper, about 1 teaspoon of each.'),
('4397', '3', 'Transfer bread crumbs to a dish and reserve.'),
('4397', '4', 'Return skillet to heat and add 3 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil, 3 turns of the pan.'),
('4397', '5', 'Add sardines and red pepper flakes to the pan and saute over medium heat 2 or 3 minutes.'),
('4397', '6', 'Add hot, cooked pasta to the skillet and toss with sardines.'),
('4397', '7', 'Add bread crumbs to the pot and toss thoroughly to combine and evenly distribute the mixture. Taste, to adjust seasonings, and serve.'),
('4398', '1', 'Boil Pasta in 5 cups of water with 1 tablespoon salt and 1 tablespoon olive oil for 12 minutes. Put in Udong Noodles after boiling pasta for 7 minutes. After 12 minutes, pour pasta/noodles into strainer and pour ice cold water on it. set aside. (Make sure you put the pasta when the water is already boiling, that''s when the 12 minutes boiling starts).For the sauce -- put 3-4 tablespoons olive oil in a non-stick pan and saute garlic and onions. Then add tomatoes until soft pulp remains.'),
('4398', '2', 'Add Beef Bouillon Cube and Sardines. Then add spices: oregano, sage, ground black pepper & bell pepper.whisk until ingredients are well mixed.Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.'),
('4398', '3', 'Serve with the Spaghetti-Udong Noodles.'),
('4399', '1', 'Scale and gut the sardines (you can have your fishmonger do this).'),
('4399', '2', 'Wash the sardines under cold, running water and pat dry with paper towels.'),
('4399', '3', 'Lightly salt the sardines with coarse sea salt and refrigerate.'),
('4399', '4', 'Meanwhile, boil 2 potatoes until a knife is easily inserted.'),
('4399', '5', 'Drain and cool.'),
('4399', '6', 'Roast 2 green bell peppers over an open flame until charred.'),
('4399', '7', 'Place in a bowl and cover it with plastic to allow it to steam for approximately 20 minutes.'),
('4399', '8', 'Remove the plastic and peel and seed the peppers.'),
('4399', '9', 'Cut peppers into 3-inch wide strips and combine in bowl with 1/4 cup of olive oil, 1/8 cup white wine vinegar, onion, and garlic.'),
('4399', '10', 'Add tomato (sliced) , onion (sliced) and cucumber. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.'),
('4399', '11', 'Preheat a grill or barbecue.'),
('4399', '12', 'Place the sardines on a hot grill'),
('4399', '13', 'When the sardines are done on first side'),
('4399', '14', 'Place 4 sardines on each plate with 2 potato halves and some green pepper salad.'),
('4399', '15', 'For decoration and extra flavour, drizzle with remaining olive oil.'),
('4400', '1', 'Scale and gut the sardines (you can have your fishmonger do this).Wash the sardines under cold, running water and pat dry with paper towels.Lightly salt the sardines with coarse sea salt and refrigerate.Meanwhile, boil 2 potatoes until a knife is easily inserted.'),
('4400', '2', 'Drain and cool.Roast 2 green bell peppers over an open flame until charred.'),
('4400', '3', 'Place in a bowl and cover it with plastic to allow it to steam for approximately 20 minutes.'),
('4400', '4', 'Remove the plastic and peel and seed the peppers.'),
('4400', '5', 'Cut peppers into 3-inch wide strips and combine in bowl with 1/4 cup of olive oil, 1/8 cup white wine vinegar, onion, and garlic.'),
('4400', '6', 'Add tomato (sliced) , onion (sliced) and cucumber. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.Preheat a grill or barbecue.'),
('4400', '7', 'Place the sardines on a hot grill'),
('4400', '8', 'When the sardines are done on first side'),
('4400', '9', 'Place 4 sardines on each plate with 2 potato halves and some green pepper salad.For decoration and extra flavour, drizzle with remaining olive oil.'),
('4401', '1', 'Divide everything evenly and arrange on individual plates, making sure that you roll the individual meats and cheese slices.If you have seafood forks, place a seafood fork by each plate. If not, a salad fork will do.This is served in place of a salad as an individual course.'),
('4402', '1', 'Cut fish into 1" pieces.'),
('4402', '2', 'Saute garlic in olive oil over medium heat until golden.'),
('4402', '3', 'Add sardines and continue to saute and stir until almost a paste (approximately 7 minutes).'),
('4402', '4', 'Add tomato paste and 3 to 5 tomato paste cans of water to the fish and bring to boil.'),
('4402', '5', 'Add herbs (leaves only)and raisins.Reduce heat, add salt and pepper. simmer until thick.'),
('4402', '6', 'Place cold water into large pot and start to the boil.Boil pasta until al dente, drain and toss with sauce.'),
('4402', '7', 'Serve with grated cheese on the side.'),
('4403', '1', 'Mix the oil and vinegar for the dressing, add salt, pepper and the herbs.Toss together carefully, the dressing, beans, eggs (keep one for the garnish), onion, tomatoes, tuna, garlic and half of the olives. add salt and pepper to taste.Pile in the center of the serving dish on top of the lettuce leaves, make it look as attractive as possible, finish the salad with the garnish ingredients.'),
('4406', '1', 'In a large bowl, combine the soy sauce, sugar, and 1/4 cup of the oil. In a small bowl, combine the cornstarch and chicken stock. Set both aside.Make three slashes on the skin side of each salmon fillet, cutting halfway into the fish.'),
('4406', '2', 'Place the salmon in a shallow dish and pour the soy-sauce marinade over it. Refrigerate for 30 minutes.In a medium saucepan, heat the remaining 1/4 cup of oil over medium heat and add the garlic, ginger, and black bean sauce. Cook for 1 to 2 minutes, or until the garlic is golden.'),
('4406', '3', 'Add the vinegar and the cornstarch mixture. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer. Cook for 10 minutes, remove from heat, and keep warm.'),
('4406', '4', 'Remove the fish from the marinade and place on a foil-lined broiler pan, about 3 inches from the heat. Broil 3 to 4 minutes per side, until just cooked through (center should be slightly translucent).'),
('4406', '5', 'Serve the salmon over Ginger White Rice topped with the sauce and the raw vegetables.'),
('4411', '1', '1Sprinkle the salmon fillets with a little salt.'),
('4411', '2', 'Put the wine, water, dill, parsley and shallots or onionsin a saut pan, and bring to a simmer on medium heat.2'),
('4411', '3', 'Place salmon fillets, skin-side down on the pan. Cover. Cook 5 to 10 minutes, depending on the thickness of the fillet, or to desired done-ness. Do not overcook.'),
('4411', '4', 'Serve sprinkled with freshly ground black pepper and a slice or two of lemon.'),
('4417', '1', 'Whisk the sesame seeds, miso, mirin, and sugar together with a fork (you might need to use the back of the fork to mash up the miso a little first).'),
('4417', '2', 'Add the mint, cilantro and garlic stir to combine.If you''re BBQing, get your fire going and make sure you have a cooler area of the fire to put the fish on.If you''re using the broiler, put your oven rack in the middle of the oven and turn the broiler on high. Get a pan with a wire rack on top ready (I just use a shelf out of the toaster oven on top of a baking sheet).Just before you''re ready to throw the salmon in the oven, give it a nice thick coating of glaze, especially on top (the meat side).'),
('4417', '3', 'Place the salmon, on the rack, skin side down.Cook until the glaze is nice and brown and the salmon is just barely translucent at it''s thickest part 7-12 minutes depending on the thickness of the salmon and the temperature of your heat source. If the glaze starts to burn before the salmon is done, lay a piece of foil on top of the salmon.'),
('4420', '1', 'Preheat a gas grill to high. adjust to medium low after 15 minutes. (If cooking over charcoal, allow the coals to burn until they are covered with white ash.)'),
('4420', '2', 'Place the salmon skin-side down on the cedar plank.'),
('4420', '3', 'Combine the brown sugar, oil, thyme, and cayenne in a bowl.'),
('4420', '4', 'Spread over the salmon.'),
('4420', '5', 'Place the planked salmon on the grilling grate and cook, with grill covered, about 40 minutes or just until the surface fat begins to turn white.Rainy-Day Method: Preheat oven to 325 F. Prepare the salmon as described above, then roast on the cedar plank for about 25 minutes.'),
('4422', '1', 'Bake for 45 minutes to an hour or until the fish is cooked when you look down each score mark to the bone.'),
('4422', '2', 'Serve warm, at room temperature or chilled.'),
('4423', '1', 'In a small saucepan over medium heat combine brown sugar, lemon zest, lemon juice, garlic, green onion, soy sauce, olive oil, and ginger. Cook until sugar is dissolved and mixture is fragrant.'),
('4423', '2', 'Remove from heat, stir in orange juice.'),
('4423', '3', 'Place fish and marinade mixture into a resealable plastic bag. Refrigerate overnight, or for at least 3 hours.Preheat grill for medium direct heat. Lightly oil grill grate.'),
('4423', '4', 'Remove salmon from resealable bag and pour remaining marinade into a small saucepan. Bring marinade to a boil. Reduce heat and let simmer until slightly thickened, 5-10 minutes.Cook salmon for 6 to 8 minutes per side, or until the fish flakes easily with a fork.'),
('4423', '5', 'Garnish with reduced marinade sauce and chopped green onion.'),
('4424', '1', 'Pour the lemon juice, broth and cream into a small pot and bring to a simmer. Immediately drop the heat to low, cover the pot and simmer very gently for 10 minutes.'),
('4424', '2', 'Add salt and pepper to taste.2 While the sauce is cooking, rinse the salmon in cold water and check for any stray scales (if skin-on). Pat the fish dry with paper towels.'),
('4424', '3', 'Add the canola oil to a saut pan large enough to fit the fish in one layer. Set the heat to high and let the pan heat up for 90 seconds.3 Lay the fish skin side down in the hot pan and turn the heat down to medium. Salt the exposed side of the fish.'),
('4424', '4', 'Let this sizzle away steadily for 3-5 minutes, depending on how thick the fish is. An inch-thick fillet will take about 5 minutes. With a metal spatula, turn the fish, making sure the skin remains attached to the salmon. Salt the skin side of the fish. Cook for another 1-5 minutes, depending on how well-done you like your fish. We like our salmon a little rare in the center, so we cook the second side of a 1-inch fillet about 3 minutes.4 Set the salmon down on the plate skin side up, then pour some of the sauce over it.'),
('4424', '5', 'Garnish with the parsley and serve at once.'),
('4425', '1', 'Add everything except the chives in a bowl and work together with your fingers, breaking up the chunks of salmon as you go. There should be enough salt from the salmon, but add more if it needs it.'),
('4425', '2', 'Add the chopped chives and mix in. Allow it to rest for at least an hour and serve'),
('4427', '1', 'In a small saute pan, heat oil over medium heat and add almonds, stirring until they become fragrant, 2 to 3 minutes.'),
('4427', '2', 'Transfer to a bowl to cool, then stir in lime juice and season with salt.'),
('4427', '3', 'Mix in yogurt until fully combined. Chill until ready to use.'),
('4428', '1', 'In a bowl, combine the chili powder, oregano, and salt. Pat the spices on the fish or meat.'),
('4428', '2', 'Heat the oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat. Cook 5 minutes per side for the salmon, 8 to 10 minutes per side for the chicken, or 15 minutes per side for the pork. (Reduce the heat if the spices begin to turn black.) Divide the fish or meat among 4 plates.'),
('4429', '1', 'Heat grill to medium. Season the salmon with 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. arrange on the plank.'),
('4429', '2', 'Place the plank on the grill and cook, covered, until the salmon is opaque and flakes easily, 12 to 15 minutes. In a bowl, combine the cucumber, jalapeo, lemon juice, oil, and 1/2 teaspoon salt.'),
('4429', '3', 'Serve with the salmon.'),
('4430', '1', 'Combine lemon juice, rosemary, salt, pepper and garlic.'),
('4430', '2', 'Brush mixture onto fish.Spray the rack of a broiler pan with olive oil spray and arrange the fish on it. Broil 4 from the heat until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork, approx. 4-6 minutes per 1/2 of thickness. If fish is more than 1 thick, gently turn it halfway through broiling.Print This6 PP 7 SP Fish Recipes Lenten Friendly Recipes Main Dishes Recipes Seafood Recipesposted May 13, 2008 by Gina32 Comments'),
('4431', '1', 'Heat 1 tablespoon oil in large nonstick skillet over medium heat.'),
('4431', '2', 'Add 2/3 cup ramp bulbs and stems to skillet and saut just until soft but not browned, reducing heat if necessary to prevent browning, about 5 minutes.'),
('4431', '3', 'Transfer sauted ramps to processor (do not clean skillet).'),
('4431', '4', 'Add green tops, cheese, almonds, and tarragon to processor. process until finely chopped. With machine running, gradually add 1/2 cup oil and puree until almost smooth.'),
('4431', '5', 'Transfer pesto to bowl. Season to taste with salt and pepper. DO AHEAD Can be made 1 day ahead. cover and chill.Cook pasta in large pot of boiling salted water until just tender but still firm to bite, stirring occasionally.Meanwhile, heat remaining 1 tablespoon oil in same large skillet over medium-high heat. Sprinkle salmon with salt and pepper.'),
('4431', '6', 'Add salmon to skillet and cook just until opaque in center, about 4 minutes per side.'),
('4431', '7', 'Drain pasta, reserving 3/4 cup pasta cooking liquid. Return pasta to pot. add all but 1/4 cup pesto and toss to coat, adding enough pasta cooking liquid by tablespoonfuls to moisten. Season with salt and pepper. Divide pasta among plates. Top with salmon.'),
('4431', '8', 'Spread remaining 1/4 cup pesto over fish and serve.'),
('4432', '1', 'Preheat oven to 450 degrees. In a medium bowl, whisk together 2 tablespoons fresh lemon juice, 1 teaspoon coarse salt, and 1/4 teaspoon ground pepper.'),
('4432', '2', 'Add 3 large julienned carrots and 1/2 head shredded Napa cabbage. toss to combine.'),
('4434', '1', 'Mix the rice and 2 1/3 cups water in a medium skillet. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, for 10 minutes. Slice the salmon on a diagonal into four 3/4-inch-thick pieces. Season with 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.'),
('4434', '2', 'Place on top of the partially cooked rice. Cover and cook 7 minutes. Scatter the peas over the salmon and rice. Cover and cook until the rice and peas are tender and the salmon is opaque and beginning to flake, 3 to 5 minutes.'),
('4434', '3', 'Mix the soy sauce, scallions, vinegar, ginger, and sugar in a small bowl. Spoon the sauce over the salmon, rice, and peas and serve. Technique: You can adapt this one-pot cooking method to shrimp and scallops. ('),
('4434', '4', 'Add them with the peas, after the rice has cooked for about 15 minutes.) The key is covering the skillet, so everything steams together. If your pan doesnt have a lid, use a baking sheet.'),
('4436', '1', 'Make sauce: Stir together yogurt, chopped tarragon, lemon juice, olive oil and cucumber. season with salt and pepper.'),
('4436', '2', 'Heat broiler, with rack set 4 inches from heat. Line a rimmed baking sheet with aluminum foil.'),
('4436', '3', 'Place salmon on sheet, and season with salt and pepper. Broil until opaque throughout, 8 to 10 minutes.'),
('4436', '4', 'Serve with sauce on the side.*Note: Skip the citrus juice in portions fed to eaters under 12-months-old.'),
('4437', '1', 'In a small bowl, whisk together the teriyaki sauce, sugar, and garlic until sugar dissolves.'),
('4437', '2', 'Place salmon fillets in a large bowl and toss with marinade to coat fillets. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 30 minutes. Toss cucumbers with vinegar, cover, and refrigerate until ready to serve.'),
('4437', '3', 'Lightly coat clean grids of grill with cooking oil spray.'),
('4437', '4', 'Heat grill to medium heat.'),
('4437', '5', 'Remove salmon from marinade. Arrange salmon fillets, skin side down, evenly on grill and cover with lid. Grill without turning fillets, 8 minutes. Using a large spatula, carefully turn fillets and cook, covered, 2 to 3 minutes longer, just until salmon is cooked through but still moist and flaky.'),
('4437', '6', 'Serve with cucumber salad.'),
('4438', '1', 'Heat broiler.'),
('4438', '2', 'Whisk together the maple syrup and mustard in a small saucepan over medium heat and bring to a boil. Simmer until slightly thickened, about 5 minutes.'),
('4438', '3', 'Remove from heat and set aside.'),
('4438', '4', 'Place the salmon in a foil-lined 9-by-13-inch baking dish. Season with the salt and pepper. Slice the peel from the pineapple half and cut it lengthwise into quarters, then cut each quarter into 1/2-inch-thick triangles. Scatter the pineapple and jalapeo around the salmon.'),
('4438', '5', 'Brush the salmon with the syrup mixture. Broil for 5 to 7 minutes, or until the salmon flakes easily when pricked with a fork and the inside is the same color throughout.'),
('4438', '6', 'Serve the salmon and pineapple with the rice and drizzle with the remaining glaze, if desired.Tip: Slice the other half of the pineapple left over from this recipe, brush it with maple syrup, and broil until it bubbles.'),
('4438', '7', 'Serve with ice cream.'),
('4439', '1', '1 Preheat the oven to 400F (convection or regular). Set the salmon on a foil-lined baking sheet skin side down. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.2 In a small bowl, combine the honey mustard and 1 teaspoon of the thyme. In another small bowl, mix the panko with the remaining 1 teaspoon of thyme, 4 teaspoons of olive oil, parsley, and paprika.'),
('4439', '2', 'Add salt and pepper (a light sprinkle).3 Using a small spoon, spread the mustard mixture on the salmon. top with the bread crumb mixture. 4 Roast the salmon for 12-14 minutes (test at 1'),
('4439', '3', 'or until it is almost completely firm to the touch and flakes when poked with a fork.'),
('4439', '4', 'Serve at once.'),
('4440', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 400 degrees.'),
('4440', '2', 'Cut the greens off the beets, leaving about  inch of the stems still attached. Save the greens for another time. Wash the beets well and place them in a roasting pan with a -inch layer of water on the bottom. Cover tightly with foil (if the foil touches the beets, cover first with parchment, then with foil.) Roast about 50 minutes (or longer for larger beets). When the beets are done, carefully remove the foil. Allow them to cool, and then peel them by slipping off the skins with your fingers.'),
('4440', '3', 'Cut them into -inch wedges.Slice the stem and bottom ends from the blood oranges. Stand the oranges on one end and, following the contour of the fruit with a very sharp knife, remove the peel and white pith. Work from top to bottom, rotating the fruit as you go. Then hold each orange over a bowl and carefully slice between the membranes and the fruit to release the segments in between. Squeeze any juice left in the remaining membrane into a measuring cup.'),
('4440', '4', 'Add any juice from the bowl of blood orange segments to the measuring cup. (Or if you''re pressed for time, just slice the oranges into rounds.)'),
('4440', '5', 'Combine the diced shallot, lemon juice,  cup blood orange juice (if you didnt reserve enough, you can add regular freshly squeezed orange juice), honey and  teaspoon salt in a small bowl.'),
